name: D-sedoheptulose 7-phosphate isomerase
classes: Interconverting aldoses and ketoses, and related compounds
comment: In Gram-negative bacteria the enzyme is involved in biosynthesis of ADP-L-glycero-beta-D-manno-heptose, which is utilized for assembly of the lipopolysaccharide inner core. In Gram-positive bacteria the enzyme is involved in biosynthesis of GDP-D-glycero-alpha-D-manno-heptose, which is required for assembly of S-layer glycoprotein.
